channel.title: Net neutrality for Americans has been killed
channel.description:
:sob: Net neutrality is now dead in the USA :sob: :us: :computer:
The FCC has voted to remove net neutrality laws that created an even playing field on the internet. Now telcom companies such as Verizon, AT&T, etc can restrict your access to the internet. They can also slow down or speed up certain websites depending on how much the website and you pay them. This is awful for the free internet and awful for users. Take action here: https://www.battleforthenet.com/
-Hum4n01d
[details="Previously"]
"We have just days. The FCC is about to vote to end net neutrality—breaking the fundamental principle of the open Internet—and only an avalanche of calls to Congress can stop it. So this Tuesday, December 12th, "Break the Internet" on your site, Twitter, Facebook, Snapchat, Instagram, LinkedIn, reddit, Tumblr, Youtube or in whatever wild creative way you can to get your audience to contact Congress. That’s how we win. Are you in?"
Please change your profile pics to this and spread the message around.![stopthefcc-profile-pic|500x500](upload://oc68ZdvGdYGwA3701nzfxYOLy5p.png) [/details]

item.title: Net neutrality for Americans has been killed
item.dc:creator: TheRealJFalc
item.description:
It could be affected. What if your ISP wants to promote its own inferior streaming service? It can slow down access to SC to make its own service “load” faster and seem better. Users will either deal with the frustration or switch out of anger.

This actually has happened before. Some providers slowed down access to apple pay to promote their own wireless payment service. And got caught on it. That’s why these rulings were put into place in the first place in some regards. So this wouldn’t happen again.
